```java
// This is a Java program to calculate total cost of an order based on product details and quantity.

import java.util.HashMap;
import java.util.Map;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        // Initialize price list
        Map<String, Integer> priceList = new HashMap<>();
        priceList.put("product1", 100);
        priceList.put("product2", 200);
        priceList.put("product3", 300);

        String orderString = "orderDetails–quantity";
        String[] orderData = orderString.split("\\s+");
        String[] productDetails = orderData[0].split("–");

        int productPrice = priceList.get(productDetails[1]);
        int orderQuantity = Integer.parseInt(orderData[1]);
        int orderPrice = orderQuantity * productPrice;

        System.out.println("Total cost of the order: " + orderPrice);
    }
}
```

In this code, we first initialize a `HashMap` to store product details and their prices. Then we split the order string into an array of strings using whitespace as delimiter (`\\s+`). After that, we split each order detail into separate parts based on the `–` delimiter. We then get the price for the product from the `priceList` map and calculate the total cost of the order by multiplying the quantity with the price.

