```java
// This is a Java program to calculate total cost of an order based on product details and price list.

import java.util.HashMap;
import java.util.Map;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        String orderString = "2–dune coon";
        String priceListString = "dune coon:100\nsword:200\ndisc:50";

        Map<String, Integer> priceList = new HashMap<>();
        for (String line : priceListString.split("\n")) {
            String[] parts = line.split(":");
            priceList.put(parts[0], Integer.parseInt(parts[1]));
        }

        String[] orderData = orderString.split("-");
        String[] productDetails = orderData[0].split(" ");
        int productPrice = priceList.get(productDetails[1]);
        int orderPrice = Integer.parseInt(orderData[1]) * productPrice;

        System.out.println("Total cost of the order: " + orderPrice);
    }
}
```

This program first splits the `orderString` into an array `orderData` where each element is a part of the order (the quantity and the product). Then it splits the first element of `orderData` into `productDetails`, which is an array where the first element is the product name and the second element is its quantity. It then retrieves the price for this product from the `priceList`. Finally, it calculates the total cost of the order by multiplying the quantity with the price and prints it out.

