public class RefactorWithVarArgsBug {
    // This class represents a bug where varargs method parameters are not preserved in the instance variable

	public static void main(String[] args) {
			RefactorWithVarArgsBug o = new RefactorWithVarArgsBug(true);
	}

	public RefactorWithVarArgsBug(boolean a, String... strings) {
        // This constructor takes a boolean parameter and any number of string parameters
		this.a = a;
		if (strings != null) {
			for(String str : strings){
				this.strings.add(str);  // Preserving the varargs parameter by adding them to the list
			}
		}
	}

	private boolean a; 
    private List<String> strings = new ArrayList<>(); // This is used to preserve the varargs parameter

	public boolean getA() {
        return this.a;
	}

	public List<String> getStringList() {
        return this.strings;
	}
} 
```
In this refactored code, we have preserved the varargs parameters by adding them to a list in the constructor. The `getA()` method is used to retrieve the boolean parameter and the `getStringList()` method is used to retrieve the list of string parameters.

