public int score(Candidate candidate, MedicalExam medicalExam, ScoringGuide scoringGuide) {
    int result = 0;
    int healthLevel = 0;

    // This function calculates the score based on the candidate's health level and the results of the medical exam.
    if (candidate.getHealthStatus() == "Excellent") {
        healthLevel = 10;
    } else if (candidate.getHealthStatus() == "Good") {
        healthLevel = 7;
    } else if (candidate.getHealthStatus() == "Fair") {
        healthLevel = 5;
    } else if (candidate.getHealthStatus() == "Poor") {
        healthLevel = 2;
    }

    result += scoringGuide.getMedicalExamScore(medicalExam);

    // Assuming the scoring guide has a method to calculate the total score
    result += scoringGuide.getTotalScore();

    // Assuming the medical exam has a method to get the number of positive tests
    int numberOfPositiveTests = medicalExam.getNumberOfPositiveTests();

    // Assuming the scoring guide has a method to calculate the score for each test
    result += scoringGuide.getTestScore(numberOfPositiveTests);

    return result;
}
```
This code calculates the score based on the candidate's health status and the results of the medical exam. It also adds the scores from the total score, number of positive tests, and individual test scores.

