public int score(Candidate candidate, MedicalExam medicalExam, ScoringGuide scoringGuide) {
    int result = 0; // This variable will hold the final score.
    int healthLevel = 0; // This variable holds the calculated health level based on the candidate and medical exam.

    // Calculate the health level. The formula used here is a simple example.
    if (candidate.getAge() < 18) {
        healthLevel += 10;
    } else if (candidate.getAge() >= 18 && candidate.getAge() <= 65) {
        healthLevel += 20;
    } else {
        healthLevel += 30;
    }

    // Assuming that the medical exam has a method to get the score.
    int medicalScore = medicalExam.getMedicalScore(candidate);

    // The scoring guide provides different scores for each level of medicalScore.
    if (medicalScore < scoringGuide.getLowerLimit()) {
        result += 0;
    } else if (medicalScore >= scoringGuide.getLowerLimit() && medicalScore <= scoringGuide.getUpperLimit1()) {
        result += 5;
    } else if (medicalScore > scoringGuide.getUpperLimit1() && medicalScore <= scoringGuide.getUpperLimit2()) {
        result += 10;
    } else {
        result += 15;
    }

    // Add the health level to the score.
    result += healthLevel;

    return result; // Return the final score.
}
```
This code calculates a basic health level based on age and then uses the scoring guide to assign scores to medical exam results. The final score is the sum of all calculated values.

