```java
// This is a Java program to calculate total cost of an order based on product details and quantity.

import java.util.HashMap;
import java.util.Map;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        String orderString = "2–10";
        String priceListString = "100–20 200–30 300–50";

        // Split the order string into orderData array
        String[] orderData = orderString.split("-");
        int quantity = Integer.parseInt(orderData[1]);

        // Split the price list string into a map of product details and prices
        Map<String, Integer> priceList = new HashMap<>();
        String[] priceDetails = priceListString.split(" ");
        for (String detail : priceDetails) {
            String[] parts = detail.split("-");
            priceList.put(parts[0], Integer.parseInt(parts[1]));
        }

        int productPrice = priceList.get(orderData[0]);
        int orderPrice = quantity * productPrice;

        System.out.println("Total cost of the order: " + orderPrice);
    }
}
```

This program first splits the `orderString` into an array `orderData`, where the first element is the product name and the second element is the quantity. It then retrieves the price for this product from the `priceList`. Finally, it calculates the total cost of the order by multiplying the quantity with the product price.

